1.title: Étude des moeurs
1.plot: Three young people in school. Helping Oli, Louis discovers, thanks to Thomas that modern mathematics is full of trick questions.

2.title: Le retour
2.plot: It's the end of the holidays. Louis and Nathalie sympathize with their children who must be a reason.

3.title: Devine qui vient garder ce soir
3.plot: Nathalie and Louis learn that they must replace their nanny. Zoe, Amelia and Ophelia seem to be making a good impression, but Natalie is not certain.

4.title: Qu'est-ce qu'on mange
4.plot: A daily challenge Natalie: How to prepare a meal taking into account the tastes and whims of four guys?

5.title: Et moi, et moi, émois
5.plot: Louis finds that it would be good for Oli to care for a pet. However, he's uncertain that the rest of the family will think so too.

6.title: Je crois, tu crois, ils croissent!
6.plot: Zak is old enough to cross the two blocks that separate home and school, but can he make his lunch before the parents get up?

7.title: Scènes de la vie conjugale
7.plot: Louis barely find the words, when Oli asks him to explain the secrets of orgasm, physical love and all things to do with love.

8.title: Cash-Cash
8.plot: The children are impressed to see on a photo that Louis and Natalie have previously owned a Porsche.

9.title: Génies en herbe
9.plot: Waking up to hockey practice at 5 o'clock in the morning, Louis and Oli realize something important. Louis is happy to see that Thomas has convictions.

10.title: C'est pas toujours un cadeau
10.plot: Christmas Magic and family holiday time. Natalie and Louis provided an update on the gifts they will offer to their three kids.

11.title: Frissons parentaux
11.plot: Even with adorable children like Zak, Oli and Thomas, the parental daily brings with it, turmoil.

12.title: Histoire de ménage
12.plot: Parental commotion...Louis and Natalie decided to make a garage sale involving everyone.

13.title: Violences conjuguées
13.plot: Even in the best families, patience has its limits. Between Oli and Zak, they're jostling all the time, especially when they compete for the remote control.

14.title: La blonde de Thomas
14.plot: Thomas presents his girlfriend Tamara, from the Caribbean, to his parents. Natalie feels that Louis is uncomfortable and wonders if she should mention something.

15.title: Consommation, quand tu nous tiens
15.plot: The family home is being barraged with items...Trampoline, hockey net, computer - Children will find an inexhaustible source of inspiration to encourage spending.

16.title: Parents à 110 %
16.plot: Family life is fun, especially when we find ourselves at the grocery store with the two youngest. Returning from a business trip, Natalie must care for Oli who injured his hand in playing football.

17.title: Dépendances
17.plot: Louis is distraught, after he discovered two cigarettes in a box of crayons. He can't help wondering if Thomas is now involved in drugs.

18.title: Ben, Flash et Cie
18.plot: Benoit is at home with his two-month daughter and it seems Louis has more maternal instincts that he has been willing to let on. Zak was given the rabbit from class for a few days.

19.title: Lâche relâche
19.plot: It's finally spring break, where the culmination of work and balancing the family begins. Louis and Natalie argue about who will stay at home with the children.

20.title: No vacancy
20.plot: It's vacation time. Natalie tries to convince Louis to send the guys to camp. Though the family had planned to go to the Magdalen Islands, Louis thinks they should spend a few days in Florida.

1.title: Le retour de la rentrée
1.plot: Natalie moves heaven and Earth to find pencils specified by the school. At the table, Thomas impresses with his knowledge of the virtues of broccoli. A discussion on God allows Zak to surprise his mother with a nice compliment.

2.title: Adorables ados
2.plot: Zak knows exactly how to react to a classmate who claims to be his girlfriend. Natalie is exasperated by Thomas' attitude. With all this girl drama, Oli is now, close to the age of wanting a girlfriend also.

3.title: Humidités relatives
3.plot: Alerted by foul smell, Louis and Natalie fear water damage, but cannot find the cause. Natalie feels hurt when her Zak asks for privacy. Louis-Paul and Benoit discover Oli does not share their passion for sport on TV. by a-movie-fan.

4.title: Incompétences transversales
4.plot: Louis and Natalie's limits are tested when Oli, wants the latest model iPod. Natalie has asked Louis-Paul to go to the parents meeting, while Zak must write a text on the most extraordinary person he has known. Who will choose?

5.title: Quatre gars une fille
5.plot: With a professional obligation to attend too, Natalie asks the boys to prepare their lunch. At the grocery store, Natalie is annoyed that no-one is prepared to lift a finger to help with the overload.

6.title: Fric, frasques, troc
6.plot: Thomas has decided he can be the boss of the children. However, Louis-Paul and Natalie are not convinced he's ready for the responsibility. Returning from a walk, Natalie and Louis-Paul are concerned when Zak and Oli are not at home.

7.title: La valse des citrouilles
7.plot: Halloween is an exciting time for the family. Zak relies on the help of his brothers to dress up, while Thomas believes he is too old for Halloween. Louis-Paul seeks a way to trick the small neighbors while going to the hockey.

8.title: Le petit vient en mangeant
8.plot: Tired of seeing the boys sulk at dinner, due to their eating too much after school, a solution must be made. Fortunately for boys, they can count on the solidarity of their father. Oli explains his theory of delayed motivation to his dad.

9.title: Cacaphonies
9.plot: Natalie cannot find the pot of hot sauce. Zak and Oli have an urgent need to drink. Louis-Paul is snoring like a bear and it is tormenting everyone in the house. Natalie wants Oli and Thomas to help prepare the meal.

10.title: Les patentes à gosses
10.plot: With the TV and everything that connects to it, is highly valued, yet still, no-one knows how to use the remote control. Natalie is desperate to convince Zak to forgo his old jeans, that are full of holes, just for the school photo.

11.title: Dehors novembre
11.plot: Louis-Paul must resort to collective bartering when he asks for help to pick up the dead leaves. Zak insists he is going to register with the hockey League. It is time to pack up the winter clothes, but the boys are not in a good mood.

12.title: L'éveil de Noël
12.plot: Louis and Natalie find a way to determine which boy will make which gift. Feeling that his father is showing signs of aging, Thomas offers his father some computer software that will help stimulate his mind.

13.title: Métro, boulot, ado
13.plot: Louis-Paul and Natalie, exhausted, can happily afford a nice and relaxing, weekend for two. However, they have to think seriously before going. as they still need to make sure the children lack nothing.

14.title: Y a-t-il un pilote à l'urgence?
14.plot: Zak complains about an unbearable stomach ache. Natalie takes him to the emergency room, but does not leave empty-handed. To add insult to injury, Oli is injured from falling down the stairs.

15.title: Les beaux discours
15.plot: A discussion begins due a pamphlet on virginity that Thomas has brought home from the Church. It's soon clear, it's a very hard topic to put into words for the three boys to understand, while at the table.

16.title: Faits d'hiver
16.plot: Benoit joins the family for a street hockey game while Louis-Paul teaches the art of throwing snowballs to Zak and Oli. However, now that it's winter, when the time comes to start the car, it is Thomas who has a few things to show them.

17.title: Six pieds dans le trouble
17.plot: Natalie learns that her uncle Roger is dead. It is the first time the Parent family have had to mourn anyone. Natalie and Louis-Paul wonder how children will react to this sudden loss.

18.title: Garsmasinage & cie
18.plot: Natalie has been practicing yoga via DVD, and her progress has been very impressive. However, the boys are exasperated, seeing their TV being used non-stop. But, will they convince Louis-Paul to purchase a new TV?

19.title: Brutus
19.plot: After a lightning strike, Marie tells her story to Natalie, is shocked. Louis-Paul and Natalie have decided to spend a week in the South, without the children...But she has concerns. Zak tries to convince Natalie to adopt a dog.

20.title: Bernie & Maddie
20.plot: Natalie's parents, Madeleine and Bernard, do not come empty-handed when they are invited to dinner. They await the opportunity to reward their grandsons, while Louis and Natalie are seem unhappy.

21.title: Les papas pêcheurs se recyclent au bac
21.plot: Zak upsets Louis-Paul and Natalie, when he announces the soccer tournament, could be extended until Sunday. Louis-Paul had planned a fishing expedition for sometime now.

22.title: Cocos en fête
22.plot: Thomas arrives at home on his friends new scooter. It doesn't take much for him to realize he would like to have one of his own. Natalie wants to go with the family to the sugar shack.

23.title: Les homards se mangent à la perceuse
23.plot: Playing Rock Band, the guys make too much noise. Fed up with it all, Natalie decides to pull out the battery. Zak is frustrated because they refuse to buy him a dog, or adopt one.

24.title: Les rois de la patate
24.plot: Thomas and his parents agree it is time for him to be responsible enough to hold down a summer job? But where? In a fast food chain? Why not at the office of Natalie?

1.title: Vive les vacances
1.plot: The Parents are in dire need of a break, so they rent a lovely cottage to relax and put their feet up. However, the boys feel the opposite and then the rain decides to ruin their parade.. Keeping the boys busy inside, is far from relaxing.

2.title: Anais
2.plot: Thomas has a new girlfriend. Hesitant to invite her to his home, she eventually meets the family, in all their glory. The parents are bravely planning to have 'the 'birds and the bees' talk with Thomas. What will his reaction be?

3.title: Métro boulot sandwich
3.plot: As the holidays draw to a close, Natalie's dreading going home and diving back into the same boring routine of everyday life. Louis-Paul and Natalie have enrolled Oli in a Private school, in the hope, he'll overcome some of his problems.

4.title: Conseil de famille
4.plot: Both Louis-Paul and Natalie, are going to recommend, they have regular family meetings. With the boys unhappy with certain rules, this would be a good way for everyone to sort out any issues.

5.title: Ados a pitons
5.plot: Natalie and Louis-Paul, have decided to give Thomas a mobile phone. However, having a phone, comes with conditions, courtesy of his parents. Typically, Oli thinks it is unfair he doesn't get one, while Zak, has his own problem...boredom.

6.title: Bonne conduite
6.plot: Young Thomas is as determined as ever to pass his learner's driving test. So much so, he spends as much time in the garage, practicing. Soon, with dad by his side, he makes his way onto the highway in the family van.

7.title: Blues d'automne
7.plot: It's fall, and everyone's got a touch of the blues. So, Marie has a plan, that involves Natalie, a plane and New York City. The boys are at an age, where appearance is everything. However, having one bathroom, can cause untold chaos.

8.title: Virtuellement ami
8.plot: Facebook, it seems, is causing dramas between, Marie, Natalie, Oli and Zak. Thomas has convinced Anaïs, to spend the evening at his home. Oli and Zak are having trouble sleeping. So, acting out scenes from horror movies, makes sense...no?

9.title: Ados Sapiens
9.plot: Natalie volunteers to fold sheets, for a good cause. Oli and friends go to a late-night movie. Louis-Paul decides to pick them all up, not wanting Oli to take a bus so late. A Policeman visits the home, after an emergency call was received.

10.title: Crise d'ado
10.plot: The Parent's are held captive by Thomas' adolescent crisis. He's not a morning person, he hogs the bathroom, and when hungry, becomes impossible to please. Though frustrated, Zak's proud of Thomas' training. He arm wrestles with his father.

11.title: Tout-compris
11.plot: Natalie and Louis-Paul, jet off on a 7-day holiday, in the sunny South. The boys pleaded to be left alone at home, but their request fell on deaf ears. They're now left, in the loving hands of Natalie's parents, Bernard and Madeleine.

12.title: La réalité dépasse la friction
12.plot: Natalie tries to teach Thomas ironing, but he'd rather be with his father. Both Oli and Thomas are upset that Zak is spoiled for his age. Oli announces he wants to become a CEO and Thomas is worried, as Anais has not contacted him in days.
